name: Italian Air Force Boeing KC-767 Tanker Close Up Departure from Calgary Airport
description:
Every summer, generally during the first week of July, NATO troops come to Calgary to train at Suffield, a Canadian Forces Base southeast of Calgary. The French, Belgian, and German Air Forces already came and went this year, but this Italian Air Force KC-767 was a pretty unique visitor! Here we have MM62229 taxiing out from Apron 6 and departing runway 35L heading back to Europe. I didn't hear what airport they were cleared to unfortunately, but I hope you enjoy this military 767 up close, with ATC included!

Thanks for watching!
